title._content: > Peak 5308 and the West Portal Entrance to the Atigun Gorge From a Point South of Galbraith Camp...08/1973

description._content: Original Caption: Peak 5308 and the West Portal Entrance to the Atigun Gorge From a Point South of Galbraith Camp. Galbraith Lake Appears in the Center of the Frame. The Pipeline Will Go From North to South, Left to Right between the Lake and the Peaks in the Distance. Mile 140 Alaska Pipeline Route 08/1973 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-7941 Photographer: Cowals, Dennis, 1945- Subjects: Alaska (United States) state Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=550426 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
